Until I really made a survey of cemetery EVPs--listening to every  
example I could find--I assumed that we were all met by loved ones or  
higher beings or whatever, but it does seem as if a lot of people  
have no personal guardian who takes them across--whatever that means.  
Especially kids. One would think there would be legions of angels or  
something for them. But...

I dunno. It&#39;s one of those things about the After Life that I don&#39;t  
understand. And the very imperfection of the situation makes me think  
it is true.

Ann

